### Event: Vault Challenge at SAINTCON

#### Overview
- **Title**: Vault Challenge
- **Presented by**: k4ffn8 and rev
- **Description**: The Vault is the premier physical penetration test challenge at SAINTCON, designed for those skilled in bypassing security measures. Participants will work to infiltrate a simulated high-security environment while avoiding detection and leaving no trace.

#### Challenge Details
- **Theme**: The challenge incorporates both physical and digital elements, with scenarios and materials crafted using generative AI technology.
- **Scenario**: Competitors will simulate a heist where they embody a team tasked with stealing proprietary data from a rival corporation called Zenith Applied Sciences, while overcoming layered security obstacles.

#### Contest Format & Rules
- **Practice Runs**:
  - **Tuesday**: 10:30 AM - 5:00 PM
  - **Wednesday**: 10:30 AM - 1:00 PM
- **Qualifying Runs**:
  - **Wednesday**: 1:00 PM - 5:00 PM
  - **Thursday**: 10:30 AM - 1:00 PM
- **Finals**:
  - **Thursday**: 1:00 PM - 5:00 PM

#### How It Works
- **Duration**: Each run typically lasts 15 minutes. Teams must exit the area within this time to avoid being "caught" by security.
- **Entry Methods**: Destructive entry is prohibited; all physical objects must remain intact.
- **Off-limits Areas**: Areas marked with yellow tape are off-limits.

#### Scoring & Prizes
- Points are awarded based on the complexity of security measures accessed. In case of a tie, the team with the fastest exit wins.
- **Team Composition**: Teams can consist of 1-4 members.

#### Hours of Operation
- **Monday**: Expo Closed
- **Tuesday**: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Wednesday**: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Thursday**: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- **Friday**: 9:00 AM – 10:00 AM

### Additional Information
- **Contact & Support**: Various channels are available for participant support, registration inquiries, and sponsor details.
- **For More Information**: Visit the [SAINTCON website](https://saintcon.org/con-vault-challenge/). 

This comprehensive overview highlights the key aspects of the Vault Challenge, designed for participants to engage in an immersive security test experience.